OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FPolicing boss 'not judging'
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Fthefts to feed family      
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5F                           
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, The head of policing in West Yorkshire 
OL,6, has said she would not judge someone   
OL,7, for stealing food to feed their family 
OL,8, amid the cost of living crisis.        
OL,10,FDeputy Mayor Alison Lowe told the BBC  
OL,11,Fshe understood how poverty could push  
OL,12,Fpeople to break the law.               
OL,14,FShe said: "You can't feed your family  
OL,15,Fand stealing a loaf of bread can do    
OL,16,Fthat, you know, I'm personally not     
OL,17,Fjudging."                              
OL,19,FThe force said it was committed to     
OL,20,Finvestigating reports of theft.        
